...you are the queen.

11:35.070 --> 11:37.700
Babe! Babe,
isn't this incredible?

11:37.700 --> 11:41.360
It's amazing.
I mean, this is incredi...ble.

11:41.360 --> 11:42.490
♪♪

11:42.490 --> 11:46.570
Oh...the hot tub?
So what! Who cares?

11:46.570 --> 11:47.400
I...cares.

11:47.400 --> 11:49.570
Who needs a stupid hot tub
when we have this --

11:49.570 --> 11:51.490
this whole entire ocean
to ourselves?

11:51.490 --> 11:54.280
Well, I wasn't planning
on going in the ocean.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.030
I have a head wound.

11:55.030 --> 11:56.450
I was planning on
going in the hot tub.

11:56.450 --> 11:59.110
Okay, well, change of plans,
right? Right?

11:59.110 --> 12:01.700
Come on, let's go check out
the rest of this place.

12:01.700 --> 12:03.610
[ Footsteps departing ]

12:03.610 --> 12:07.650
Martin:
[ In distance ] Oh, babe,
you got to see this remote!

12:10.990 --> 12:13.360
Martin:
Mm. Oh, my God.

12:13.360 --> 12:18.450
The ocean is like a lullaby,
just lulling you to sleep, huh?

12:18.450 --> 12:20.400
Hmm, yeah.
Yeah.

12:20.400 --> 12:21.610
Yeah.

12:21.610 --> 12:23.740
[ Chuckles ]

12:23.740 --> 12:27.530
Does this mattress
feel king-sized to you?

12:27.530 --> 12:28.610
What?

12:28.610 --> 12:32.320
The mattress that
we're currently lying on?

12:32.320 --> 12:32.860
Yeah?

12:32.860 --> 12:35.780
I'm asking,
does it feel king-sized?

12:35.780 --> 12:38.490
Yeah.
Yeah, I think so.

12:38.490 --> 12:41.280
Hmm. Interesting.

12:41.280 --> 12:43.030
[ Breathes deeply ]

12:43.030 --> 12:43.950
To me it feels cramped.

12:43.950 --> 12:47.360
Well, maybe because you've been
sleeping alone for too long.

12:47.360 --> 12:49.990
Maybe.
Maybe.

12:49.990 --> 12:52.070
Maybe not.

12:52.320 --> 12:57.700
The description said
"luxury king-sized mattress."

12:57.700 --> 12:58.200
Mm.

12:58.200 --> 13:00.200
Doesn't really
feel like either.

13:00.200 --> 13:02.820
Mm...uh-oh.

13:02.820 --> 13:04.110
Sounds like the old Lena.

13:04.110 --> 13:07.780
Well,
Old Lena has a point.

13:07.780 --> 13:08.570
Well...

13:08.570 --> 13:13.030
maybe I can take Old Lena's
mind off the mattress.

13:13.030 --> 13:16.320
Unh...
You know howshegets.

13:16.320 --> 13:17.320
Yeah.
Mm.

13:17.320 --> 13:19.820
Yeah.
I love a challenge.

13:19.820 --> 13:22.110
That's why
I married Old Lena.

13:22.110 --> 13:23.900
[ Chuckles ]

13:23.900 --> 13:25.820
And divorced her.

13:25.820 --> 13:27.950
[ Both laugh ]

13:27.950 --> 13:30.150
Well, did shelookpregnant?

13:30.150 --> 13:32.360
Well, no,
but it's probably early.

13:32.360 --> 13:34.900
Yes, but, I mean,
did she have the glow?

13:34.900 --> 13:36.950
I -- It's early for me,
but...

13:36.950 --> 13:39.150
[ Chuckles ]
...look.

13:40.200 --> 13:40.700
No.

13:40.700 --> 13:42.860
I was saying
it's none of our business.

13:42.860 --> 13:45.070
And I was saying
that it is,

13:45.070 --> 13:47.200
which is why we need you
to be the tie-breaker.

13:47.200 --> 13:48.860
Well, for a variety
of reasons,

13:48.860 --> 13:51.360
I don't think
we should mention anything

13:51.360 --> 13:52.360
unless we know for sure.

13:52.360 --> 13:56.280
Actually, not for
a variety of reasons.

13:56.280 --> 13:59.110
Just for one reason.

13:59.110 --> 14:00.900
Lena and Martin
are sleeping together.

14:00.900 --> 14:03.530
What?!
You got the hot goss
before me?

14:03.530 --> 14:04.860
I'm only
mentioning it now

14:04.860 --> 14:07.200
because I'm working
on my honesty.

14:07.200 --> 14:09.150
Speaking of which...

14:09.150 --> 14:12.110
one of you is not pulling off
that neck scarf.

14:12.110 --> 14:14.280
[ Both gasp ]
[ Growls ]

14:14.280 --> 14:16.570
♪♪

14:16.570 --> 14:18.400
Martin:
Oh, look at that.

14:18.400 --> 14:24.280
I mean, can you imagine waking
up like this every morning?

14:24.280 --> 14:25.400
I absolutely cannot.

14:25.400 --> 14:28.820
It's just --
[ Stammers ] No words.

14:28.820 --> 14:29.860
Bliss.

14:29.860 --> 14:30.900
It's bliss.

14:30.900 --> 14:31.990
Hey, babe...
[ Sighs ]

14:31.990 --> 14:34.360
...is it cool if I go
take a run on the beach?

14:34.360 --> 14:36.780
And maybe some breakfast
on the deck when I get back?

14:36.780 --> 14:38.740
Sounds great.
Unless it's gonna stress you.

14:38.740 --> 14:42.700
It won't.
No, because I-I really
want you to relax.

14:42.700 --> 14:43.320
I will!

14:43.320 --> 14:46.240
I'm gonna slip on my suit,
lounge on that deck,

14:46.240 --> 14:49.360
and see if I can make
any dolphin friends.

14:49.360 --> 14:50.740
[ Imitates dolphin ]

14:50.740 --> 14:51.490
Wow.

14:51.490 --> 14:53.490
Babe, that's like --
that's like really good.

14:53.490 --> 14:57.320
All right, I'm gonna, uh --
I'm gonna take off.

14:57.320 --> 14:58.740
I'll be back in a flash.

14:58.740 --> 15:00.240
All right.
Take your time.

15:00.240 --> 15:01.570
Okay.
Enjoy paradise!

15:01.570 --> 15:04.450
[ In distance ]
All right!

15:04.450 --> 15:05.990
♪♪

15:05.990 --> 15:08.990
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:09.200 --> 15:12.030
King-sized mattress my ass!

15:12.030 --> 15:15.610
[ Grunting ]
Where are you?

15:15.610 --> 15:18.360
♪♪

15:18.360 --> 15:19.950
Oh!

15:19.950 --> 15:26.490
♪♪

15:26.490 --> 15:28.110
Now I gotcha!

15:28.110 --> 15:31.280
♪♪

15:31.280 --> 15:33.280
Yes.

15:33.280 --> 15:34.610
Full! Ha!

15:34.610 --> 15:36.740
It's a full,
you lying sons of bitches!

15:36.740 --> 15:40.280
That's breach of contract!
That's fraud!

15:45.110 --> 15:46.990
[ Waves crashing ]

15:48.740 --> 15:49.700
Lena?

15:49.700 --> 15:52.570
Well, Kirk, I'd like to
speak with your supervisor.

15:52.570 --> 15:53.860
And don't send me
back to Patricia

15:53.860 --> 15:55.740
because we both know
she's at lunch.

15:55.740 --> 15:57.110
Kirk:Yes, ma'am.

15:57.110 --> 15:58.400
Martin! Hey!

15:58.400 --> 16:00.950
Well, well, what have we here?
[Beep]

16:00.950 --> 16:03.610
Are you okay holding
for another minute?

16:03.610 --> 16:04.700
Yes, thank you.

16:04.700 --> 16:05.360
[Beep]

16:05.360 --> 16:07.700
I don't suppose that was
one of your dolphin friends.

16:07.700 --> 16:10.070
So you just spent
the whole morning

16:10.070 --> 16:11.900
on the phone complaining
about this place?

16:11.900 --> 16:16.240
Okay, just hear me out.
It was a full.

16:16.240 --> 16:16.990
What was a full?

16:16.990 --> 16:18.700
The mattress! I was right!
It was a full!
Lena...

16:18.700 --> 16:20.450
And I texted them
pictures of the sheets

16:20.450 --> 16:22.900
and of the filthy hot tub,
and they agreed --

16:22.900 --> 16:23.740
it's not acceptable.

16:23.740 --> 16:25.530
This is the happiest
I've seen you all weekend.

16:25.530 --> 16:28.360
Woman:We're sorry. All of our
representatives are...

16:28.360 --> 16:30.530
They issued me
a case number.

16:30.530 --> 16:31.030
No.

16:31.030 --> 16:33.780
No, no. No, no, no. Don't --
Don't -- Don't touch me!

16:33.780 --> 16:35.280
Not like this.
We're on hold.

16:35.280 --> 16:36.610
I just don't get you,
Lena.

16:36.610 --> 16:38.320
You rented
this amazing place,

16:38.320 --> 16:40.650
and all you can do
is focus on what's wrong.

16:40.650 --> 16:41.820
It's like
you're missing it.

16:41.820 --> 16:44.280
I'm not missing it.
I'm fixing it.

16:44.280 --> 16:47.280
Did you even step foot
on that deck?

16:47.280 --> 16:48.240
Yes!

16:48.240 --> 16:51.450
When I took the evidence photos
of the hot tub.

16:51.450 --> 16:52.610
Uh-huh.

16:52.610 --> 16:53.700
And what about
the dolphins?

16:53.700 --> 16:56.900
Did you even talk to them,
or was that just an act?

16:56.900 --> 16:58.030
[ Imitates dolphin ]

16:58.030 --> 16:59.360
No, do-- No, no.
Too late.

16:59.360 --> 17:01.490
We're sorry.
All of our representatives...

17:01.490 --> 17:02.700
I thought things
had changed --

17:02.700 --> 17:05.450
You didn't think things changed.
You thought I changed.

17:05.450 --> 17:06.360
...remain on the line...

17:06.360 --> 17:07.530
I mean,
I'm supposed to be all,

17:07.530 --> 17:11.450
like, light and bubbly
and talking to dolphins --

17:11.450 --> 17:12.530
You brought up
the dolphins!

17:12.530 --> 17:14.950
Well, that's because I knew
it's what you wanted to hear.

17:14.950 --> 17:17.650
I'm supposed to bake buns
and lounge on the deck

17:17.650 --> 17:20.530
and, oh, shower when you shower
even if I've already showered.

17:20.530 --> 17:23.610
I asked you to shower!
I was being romantic!

17:23.610 --> 17:24.450
I know. I know.

17:24.450 --> 17:27.610
It's just -- We -- We're always
so focused on your needs

17:27.610 --> 17:31.990
that you just -- you never stop
to ask what I need.

17:32.610 --> 17:35.490
♪♪

17:35.490 --> 17:38.240
Please continue to hold...

17:38.240 --> 17:41.400
[ Sighs ]

17:41.400 --> 17:43.200
What do you need?

17:43.200 --> 17:44.570
♪♪

17:44.570 --> 17:48.200
I need you to care
about what upsets me...

17:48.200 --> 17:51.360
even if you don't
understand it.

17:51.360 --> 17:53.030
This place
was expensive.

17:53.030 --> 17:57.400
I used, like, six years
of rewards points to pay for it.

17:57.400 --> 18:00.150
And I know you don't have
the same level of investment

18:00.150 --> 18:03.320
because you didn't do
any of the heavy lifting
to get us here,

18:03.320 --> 18:08.610
but if you could just
acknowledge what's wrong...

18:08.610 --> 18:13.030
then maybe I could focus
on what's right.

18:13.030 --> 18:14.240
♪♪

18:14.240 --> 18:15.700
Patricia:Thank you for your patience.

18:15.700 --> 18:17.240
I understand
you're dissatisfied

18:17.240 --> 18:18.990
with the rental property?

18:18.990 --> 18:19.900
Very dissatisfied.

18:19.900 --> 18:22.740
Quite frankly, my dear,
this place is a dump!

18:22.740 --> 18:25.070
The main reason we rented it
was for the hot tub,

18:25.070 --> 18:25.820
and it's broken.

18:25.820 --> 18:26.900
The bed isn't
as advertised,

18:26.900 --> 18:29.610
and the downstairs bathroom
smells like a salty turd.

18:29.610 --> 18:30.950
Sorry to hear that.

18:30.950 --> 18:33.150
Not as sorry as I am
to smell it!

18:33.150 --> 18:33.950
I understand.

18:33.950 --> 18:38.570
Would a 50% refund
be satisfactory?

18:38.570 --> 18:39.400
Hold.

18:39.400 --> 18:43.110
Would a 50% refund
be satisfactory?

18:43.110 --> 18:47.150
♪♪

18:47.150 --> 18:48.530
[ Birds chirping ]

18:48.530 --> 18:52.320
[ Dog barking in distance ]

18:53.650 --> 18:55.070
Hi.

18:55.070 --> 18:55.610
What?

18:55.610 --> 18:58.070
Lisa, sorry to invade
your privacy.

18:58.070 --> 18:59.240
But we need to discuss

18:59.240 --> 19:01.950
what we saw you purchase
at the market.

19:01.950 --> 19:03.820
Cutlets?
They were on sale.

19:03.820 --> 19:05.150
I plan to freeze some
for later use.

19:05.150 --> 19:07.570
We ain't here to talk
about the cutlets, sister.

19:07.570 --> 19:10.490
We're here to talk about
the elephant in the womb.

19:10.490 --> 19:12.490
I don't know
what you're talking about.

19:12.490 --> 19:15.150
Cut the [bleep] Lisa Apple!
Are you pregnant or not?!

19:15.150 --> 19:18.650
Are the three of you aware
that Martin and I broke up?

19:18.650 --> 19:21.200
I-I knew that.
I knew that, yeah.
I didn't know that.
That's really sad.

19:21.200 --> 19:24.450
Okay, so, since Martin and I
are no longer involved,

19:24.450 --> 19:26.860
the three of you are
no longer involved.

19:26.860 --> 19:31.740
[ Southern accent ] So don't
even worry about it, y'all!

19:32.450 --> 19:34.650
[ Door slams ]
What was up
with that accent?

19:34.650 --> 19:36.150
I don't know.
What do you guys think?

19:36.150 --> 19:40.280
I think we may have to ruin
Martin and Lena's weekend.

19:40.280 --> 19:42.610
♪♪

19:42.610 --> 19:43.990
Okay, just admit it.

19:43.990 --> 19:44.860
When we were married,

19:44.860 --> 19:46.400
we were afraid
to talk about anything

19:46.400 --> 19:47.700
'cause every talk
led to a fight,

19:47.700 --> 19:51.070
and every fight felt like
it might end up in divorce.

19:51.070 --> 19:52.700
But now that
we are divorced...

19:52.700 --> 19:53.860
The pressure's off.

19:53.860 --> 19:54.570
I'm saying!

19:54.570 --> 19:58.150
It's like divorce is exactly
what our marriage needed.

19:58.150 --> 20:01.030
There's no clear signs
that say otherwise.

20:01.030 --> 20:02.900
♪♪

20:02.900 --> 20:04.780
Hi.
Hey.

20:04.780 --> 20:05.200
Hey!

20:05.200 --> 20:08.030
What's going on?
Is everything okay?

20:08.030 --> 20:10.400
Arthur.
Arthur: What's up, bro?

20:10.400 --> 20:12.360
Everything all right?

20:12.360 --> 20:16.780
Maya: We went
to see Lisa Apple.

20:17.280 --> 20:20.150
And we think
she might be pregnant.

20:20.150 --> 20:21.450
♪ I hate you ♪

20:21.450 --> 20:23.700
We don't know.

20:23.700 --> 20:25.780
♪ For what you did ♪

20:25.780 --> 20:31.150
♪ And I miss you
like a little kid ♪

20:31.150 --> 20:34.950
♪ I faked it every time ♪

20:34.950 --> 20:37.150
♪ But that's all right ♪

20:37.150 --> 20:39.860
♪ I can hardly feel anything ♪

20:39.860 --> 20:45.240
♪ I hardly feel
anything at all ♪

20:45.240 --> 20:48.070
♪♪

20:48.070 --> 20:52.740
♪ I have emotional
motion sickness ♪

20:52.740 --> 20:57.110
♪ Somebody roll
the windows down ♪

20:57.110 --> 21:01.990
♪ There are no words
in the English language ♪

21:01.990 --> 21:07.780
♪ I could scream
to drown you out ♪

21:07.780 --> 21:11.450
--Captions by VITAC--

21:11.450 --> 21:19.320
♪♪

21:21.400 --> 21:23.360
Anyway...

21:23.860 --> 21:26.780
♪♪
